VALUES ('977f65a3-8374-4120-8ea4-c710057c4a1b', '2025-12-29T22:59:42.803916', 'Follow-up Visit', 'Patient presented for follow-up regarding previous diagnoses of hyperlipidemia and hypertension, as well as management of hay fever symptoms. Blood pressure was recorded at 138/85 mmHg and heart rate was 78 bpm. Patient reported increased nasal congestion and sneezing, particularly in the morning. Recommended continuation of current antihypertensive and lipid-lowering medications, and advised using a daily intranasal corticosteroid for hay fever. Scheduled follow-up in 6 months to monitor blood pressure and lipid levels.', NULL);
